    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a museum-grade 2004 Porsche 911 (996.2) Carrera 4S, featuring the coveted wide-body silhouette and integrated rear reflector strip. This specimen is powered by a naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six M96 powerplant, delivering 315 hp through a 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. The mechanical integrity is superlative: the IMS bearing has been proactively addressed with a permanent LN Engineering Solution, and the rear main seal (RMS) remains bone dry. The all-wheel-drive system utilizes a viscous clutch to provide variable torque distribution, working in tandem with a factory-tuned suspension featuring MacPherson struts and a multi-link rear geometry for neutral turn-in characteristics. Braking is handled by four-piston monoblock calipers finished in Guards Red over cross-drilled, vented rotors. A recent DME report confirms zero ignitions in ranges 2 through 6, indicating a lifetime of sympathetic operation. Finished in flawless paint with a pristine interior, this C4S represents a pinnacle of analog feedback and mechanical purity for the serious collector.",
